---
const tedUrl = "https://www.ted.com/talks/amy_cuddy_your_body_language_may_shape_who_you_are";
const embedUrl = "https://embed.ted.com/talks/amy_cuddy_your_body_language_may_shape_who_you_are";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>TED Embed Test — HAx</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; max-width: 800px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; }
    .embed-container { position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin: 1rem 0; }
    .embed-container iframe { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0; }
    .fallback { margin-top: 1rem; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>TED Embed Test</h1>
  <p>This page validates that TED iframe embeds load correctly from the deployment domain.</p>

  <h2>Embedded TED Talk</h2>
  <div class="embed-container">
    <iframe
      src={embedUrl}
      loading="lazy"
      sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups"
      aria-label="Your body language may shape who you are by Amy Cuddy — TED Talk"
      allowfullscreen
    ></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="fallback">
    <p>If the embed above does not load, <a href={tedUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">watch on TED.com</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Test Checklist</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>[ ] Iframe renders and the TED player loads</li>
    <li>[ ] Video is playable</li>
    <li>[ ] No console errors related to X-Frame-Options or CSP</li>
    <li>[ ] Fallback link works</li>
  </ul>
</body>
</html>
